The paper focuses on the development of perception and state estimation approaches for an autonomous race car, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The use of LiDAR and camera data for perception suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely sub-category. The learning-based approaches used for color and pose estimation also suggest machine learning (cs.LG) as a possible sub-category. The use of slip dynamics for velocity estimation suggests control systems (cs.SY) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the probabilistic failure detection algorithm suggests artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as a potential sub-category.
